    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Two Campaigns, Two Misfires</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ernest G DeNegris letter disputes Sept 12 editorial criticizing Vice Pres Al Gore for accusing entertainment industry of marketing violence to children</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I am disappointed that your Sept. 12 editorial ''Unworthy Pandering by Mr. Gore'' did not mention that Al Gore and the Democrats have received significant financing from the entertainment elite. Rather than proposing more government oversight, why not go the personal-accountability route and refuse money from a group that may well be as damaging to America's youth as Big Tobacco?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I am disappointed that your Sept. 12 editorial ''Unworthy Pandering by Mr. Gore'' did not mention that Al Gore and the Democrats have received significant financing from the entertainment elite. Rather than proposing more government oversight, why not go the personal-accountability route and refuse money from a group that may well be as damaging to America's youth as Big Tobacco?</p>
        <p>If Mr. Gore wants to make a statement, he can do so in a powerful way by returning money from Hollywood.</p>
        <p>ERNEST G. DENIGRIS  Mendham, N.J., Sept. 12, 2000</p>
      </block>
